A '''relief generation''' a [[Set (mathematics)|set]] of [[landform]]s within a larger landform assembly that can be distinguished by their shape, [[geologic time scale|age]], scale and process that created them. A relief generation is typically [[Hierarchy (mathematics)|nested]] within a larger and older generation and host itself younger and smaller generations. The concept was coined by [[Julius Büdel]] in 1955.<ref name=Goudie>{{cite encyclopedia|last=Bremer|first=Hanna|editor-link=Andrew Goudie (geographer) |editor-last=Goudie|editor-first=A.S. |encyclopedia=Encyclopedia of Geomorphology |title=Relief generation|year=2004 |pages=842–843|publisher=Routledge}}</ref>
